just_use auto_player.py

# label: EARLY (auto-player)
# role: agent tool — drives a LynRummy session via Python-native hints

Fetches state, calls `strategy.build_suggestions(hand, board)`
locally, takes the top suggestion's primitives and posts each
verbatim to `/actions`. No /hint round-trip, no trick_result
on the wire — every action is a primitive.

Emission is correct-by-construction: every `merge_hand` in
`strategy.py` is routed through `_plan_merge_hand`, which looks
for a hole sized for the EVENTUAL stack and emits `move_stack`
BEFORE `merge_hand` when needed — so every intermediate frame
in replay is geometrically clean, not just the final state.
`_fix_geometry` stays as a last-ditch safety net. No settle()
belt. Terminates when the deck drops below DECK_LOW_WATER
(≈10 cards) — not on "victory" events, which are per-turn
bonuses (see `project_lynrummy_game_end_condition.md`).

## Surface

- `python3 games/lynrummy/python/auto_player.py` — fresh session.
- `--session N` — resume an existing session.
- `--max-actions N` — safety cap (default 200).

## Pointers

- Depends on: `client.py`, `strategy.py`, `geometry.py` (all same dir),
  `/actions` + `/state` + `/score` endpoints in
  `views/lynrummy_elm.go`.
- Hints architecture: client-side per `project_hints_are_client_side.md`.
  Go owns wire + referee; Python owns decomposition.

## Gesture coverage

- Intra-board primitives (`split`, `merge_stack`, `move_stack`)
  ship with a synthesized eased path via `gesture_synth`. The
  server REQUIRES `gesture_metadata.path` for these and returns
  400 without it — see `views/lynrummy_elm.go`'s
  `requiresGestureMetadata`.
- Hand-origin primitives (`merge_hand`, `place_hand`) send no
  path — `drag_endpoints` returns None because Python doesn't
  know where hand cards sit in the viewport. Elm DOM-measures
  the hand card's live rect at replay time via
  `Browser.Dom.getElement` and synthesizes from there.
